            <zone forceUpdate='true' h='9950' id='29' type-v2='text' w='51037' x='48370' y='11750'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run fontsize='14'>A lower disparity ratio does not always mean progress. In some years, the gap narrows because outcomes worsen for White women rather than improving for Black women. Disparity should be interpreted together with the actual maternal mortality rates for each group.</run>
